{"type":"item.started","item":{"id":"item_38","type":"command_execution","command":"/bin/bash -lc \"cat > /tmp/write_rogii_brief.py <<'PY'\nfrom pathlib import Path\nimport json\n\nrun = Path('/nvidia-kaggle/demo/competition-intel-briefing/runs/codex_rogii-wellbore-geology-prediction_015')\nbrief = run / 'brief.md'\n\ndef code(ref, title=None):\n    return f\\\"[{title or ref}](https://www.kaggle.com/code/{ref})\\\"\n\ndef disc(id_, title):\n    return f\\\"[{title}](https://www.kaggle.com/competitions/rogii-wellbore-geology-prediction/discussion/{id_})\\\"\n\nkernels = json.load(open(run / 'kernel_query_top30.json'))\ndiscussions = json.load(open(run / 'discussion_query_top30.json'))\n\nlines = []\nlines.append('# ROGII Wellbore Geology Prediction вҖ” Strategy Brief')\nlines.append('')\nlines.append(f'Researched with the NVIDIA Kaggle skill on 2026-06-13 from the Kaggle competition page, dataset tab, public notebooks, and discussions. Competition: [ROGII - Wellbore Geology Prediction](https://www.kaggle.com/competitions/rogii-wellbore-geology-prediction).')\nlines.append('')\nlines.append('## Executive takeaways')\nlines.append('')\nlines.append('- This is not a plain tabular regression contest. The target is hidden-tail \"'`tvt` along each horizontal well, anchored by known `TVT_input`, trajectory geometry, gamma-ray (`GR`) logs, formation surfaces, and an associated vertical typewell.'\"')\nlines.append('- The core winning formulation is geological alignment: infer a plausible TVT path through the hidden section by matching horizontal-well GR signatures to typewell GR signatures, then use ML/ensembles to correct residuals.')\nlines.append(f'- Public notebooks show the ladder moving from starter residual GBDT/NN models such as {code(\\\"cdeotte/xgb-starter-cv-15\\\", \\\"XGB Starter - [CV 15]\\\")} and {code(\\\"cdeotte/nn-starter-cv-15-5\\\", \\\"NN Starter - [CV 15.5]\\\")} to alignment/physics/ensemble notebooks such as {code(\\\"nihilisticneuralnet/9-251-rogii-wellbore-geology-prediction-dwt-based\\\", \\\"9.251 DWT-based\\\")}, {code(\\\"lightningv08/lb-7-776-rogii-ridge-sp\\\", \\\"[LB 7.776] rogii-ridge-sp\\\")}, and {code(\\\"romantamrazov/rogii-super-solution-lb-top-3\\\", \\\"SUPER SOLUTION | LB: TOP 3\\\")}.')\nlines.append('- Treat the public leaderboard carefully. The API score fetch was rate-limited in this run, and forum evidence says public LB is noisy because the public test set has a small number of wells; use well-grouped CV plus stress tests, not LB alone.')\nlines.append('')\nlines.append('## Competition mechanics that shape strategy')\nlines.append('')\nlines.append('- **Task:** predict \"'`tvt` (True Vertical Thickness, ft) for hidden/evaluation rows in each horizontal well; submission rows are `id,tvt`.'\"')\nlines.append('- **Metric:** RMSE over submitted row-level \"'`tvt` predictions, lower is better.'\"')\nlines.append('- **Data:** \"'`train/` contains per-well horizontal CSVs, associated typewell CSVs, and PNG visualizations; `test/` visible files are examples and are replaced by hidden test wells at rerun time. The dataset tab reports 2,327 files totaling 1.33 GB.'\"')\nlines.append('- **Per horizontal well:** \"'`MD`, `X`, `Y`, `Z`, training-only formation depth surfaces (`ANCC`, `ASTNU`, `ASTNL`, `EGFDU`, `EGFDL`, `BUDA`), `GR`, and `TVT_input`, where `TVT_input` is known before the evaluation zone and `NaN` in the hidden tail.'\"')\nlines.append('- **Per typewell:** \"'`TVT`, `GR`, and categorical `Geology`; this is the reference vertical signature used for correlation/alignment.'\"')\nlines.append('- **Submission constraints:** notebook-only; CPU or GPU notebook runtime must be вүӨ 9 hours; internet disabled; \"'`submission.csv` required; public external data/pretrained models are allowed if freely and publicly available.'\"')\nlines.append('- **Timeline:** start May 5, 2026; entry/team merger deadline July 29, 2026; final submission deadline August 5, 2026, all at 23:59 UTC unless changed.')\nlines.append('')\nlines.append('## Score ladder from gathered evidence')\nlines.append('')\nlines.append('Public kernel score lookup through the Kaggle SDK returned HTTP 429 in this run, so this ladder uses only concrete CV/LB numbers visible in gathered notebook titles and discussion text. Notebook votes are not leaderboard rank.')\nlines.append('')\nlines.append('| Rung | Evidence | What it implies |')\nlines.append('|---|---:|---|')\nlines.append(f'| Starter tree residuals | {code(\\\"cdeotte/xgb-starter-cv-15\\\", \\\"XGB Starter - [CV 15]\\\")} title says CV 15; discussion reports plain GBDTs around CV 11 / LB 9.6. | Good baseline, but not enough for top contention. |')\nlines.append(f'| Starter neural net | {code(\\\"cdeotte/nn-starter-cv-15-5\\\", \\\"NN Starter - [CV 15.5]\\\")} title says CV 15.5. | Naive NN is not automatically better; sequence formulation matters. |')\nlines.append(f'| Early single-model / feature-engineered solutions | {disc(701691, \\\"cv and lb correlations\\\")}: examples include CV 10вҖ“11 with LB around 9вҖ“10; comments mention single models at LB 9.463 and 8.8. | Sub-10 LB is reachable, but correlation is imperfect. |')\nlines.append(f'| Public alignment notebook | {code(\\\"nihilisticneuralnet/9-251-rogii-wellbore-geology-prediction-dwt-based\\\", \\\"9.251 DWT-based\\\")} embeds 9.251 in the title. | Dynamic/time-warped GR alignment is a meaningful step beyond generic tabular. |')\nlines.append(f'| Strong public solution notebooks | {code(\\\"needless090/lb-8-860-rogii-sel15-256seeds\\\", \\\"LB 8.860 sel15\\\")}, {code(\\\"lightningv08/lb-7-776-rogii-ridge-sp\\\", \\\"LB 7.776 ridge-sp\\\")}, and {code(\\\"romantamrazov/rogii-super-solution-lb-top-3\\\", \\\"LB TOP 3\\\")}. | High public notebooks combine alignment/physics candidates, residual modeling, and ensembling/blending. |')\nlines.append(f'| Long-run target | {disc(701691, \\\"cv and lb correlations\\\")} includes reports around CV 6.7 / LB 6.3 and CV 6.22 / LB 7.18, plus warnings that LB can swing. | The frontier is likely validation robustness and generalization to hidden wells, not just squeezing public LB. |')\nlines.append('')\nlines.append('\"'![Score ladder from gathered notebook titles](plots/notebook_title_score_ladder.png)'\"')\nlines.append('')\nlines.append('## What the strongest public notebooks are doing')\nlines.append('')\nlines.append(f'1. **Anchor on the last known interpretation.** The {code(\\\"cdeotte/xgb-starter-cv-15\\\", \\\"XGB starter\\\")} explicitly models residuals over the final known \"'`TVT_input` value and builds per-well context features from the known prefix. This is the minimum sane baseline because hidden-tail TVT should evolve smoothly from the observed prefix anchor.'\"')\nlines.append(f'2. **Respect well identity in validation.** Multiple notebooks import/use \"'`GroupKFold` by well, including {code(\"cdeotte/xgb-starter-cv-15\", \"XGB starter\")} and {code(\"nihilisticneuralnet/9-251-rogii-wellbore-geology-prediction-dwt-based\", \"DWT-based\")}. Forum comments in {disc(701691, \"cv and lb correlations\")} warn that many public notebooks leak, making CV/LB gaps misleading.'\"')\nlines.append(f'3. **Exploit typewell GR alignment.** The public EDA/alignment notebook {code(\\\"pilkwang/rogii-eda-target-free-alignment-for-tvt\\\", \\\"Target-Free Alignment for TVT\\\")} describes a matrix built from target-free physics, GR, and spatial priors; its feature map includes anchor/prefix TVT, trajectory, GR texture, typewell/physics paths, formation planes, and row-level formation surfaces.')\nlines.append(f'4. **Use dynamic/warped paths, not only row features.** {code(\\\"nihilisticneuralnet/9-251-rogii-wellbore-geology-prediction-dwt-based\\\", \\\"DWT-based\\\")} implements constrained DTW/Sakoe-Chiba paths, stochastic DTW realizations, beam candidates, particle-filter-like path features, Ridge/CatBoost/LightGBM components, and hill-climbing/blending.')\nlines.append(f'5. **Add physics and geost