f'4. **Add DTW/NCC/beam/particle-style features.** Use {code(\\\"nihilisticneuralnet/9-251-rogii-wellbore-geology-prediction-dwt-based\\\", \\\"DWT-based\\\")}, {code(\\\"mitchgansemer/drift-targeting-ncc-tree-based-rogii-wellbore\\\", \\\"Drift Targeting + NCC\\\")}, and {code(\\\"pilkwang/rogii-target-free-tvt-geosteering\\\", \\\"Geosteering\\\")} as references. The output should be several plausible TVT paths per hidden tail plus confidence features, not one brittle alignment.')\nlines.append(f'5. **Train residual models over candidate paths.** Feed anchor/prefix stats, trajectory increments, GR rolls/leads/lags, formation-surface distances, typewell/path scores, and candidate endpoints into Ridge/LightGBM/CatBoost/XGB. Public examples: {code(\\\"ravaghi/wellbore-geology-prediction-ridge\\\", \\\"Ridge\\\")}, {code(\\\"ravaghi/wellbore-geology-prediction-lightgbm\\\", \\\"LightGBM\\\")}, and {code(\\\"nihilisticneuralnet/9-251-rogii-wellbore-geology-prediction-dwt-based\\\", \\\"DWT-based\\\")}.')\nlines.append(f'6. **Blend hypotheses with out-of-fold discipline.** Use OOF predictions from distinct formulations before hill-climbing/blending; study {code(\\\"ravaghi/wellbore-geology-prediction-hill-climbing\\\", \\\"Hill Climbing\\\")}, {code(\\\"pixiux/rogii-dual-pipeline-blend\\\", \\\"Dual Pipeline Blend\\\")}, and {code(\\\"romantamrazov/rogii-super-solution-lb-top-3\\\", \\\"SUPER SOLUTION\\\")}. Avoid tuning weights purely to public LB.')\nlines.append('7. **Engineer for notebook rerun constraints.** Precompute only what rules allow via public datasets; keep inference deterministic, under 9 hours, internet-free, and robust to hidden test wells replacing the visible sample test set.')\nlines.append('')\nlines.append('## Validation risks and anti-patterns')\nlines.append('')\nlines.append(f'- **Leakage:** {disc(701691, \\\"cv and lb correlations\\\")} explicitly warns that public notebooks can have leakage and smaller CV/LB gaps. Any feature derived from validation/test hidden TVT, test IDs, or public submission artifacts should be isolated from your real OOF estimate.')\nlines.append('- **Public-LB overfit:** The same discussion reports examples where CV improvements of ~0.7 ft regressed on LB, and cases such as CV around 8 scoring 6.6 on LB. Small public test well counts can make LB lucky or unlucky.')\nlines.append(f'- **Private-set surprises:** The organizer post {disc(707695, \\\"Private Test Update and Rescore\\\")} says an outlier private test well was removed from scoring. That is a reminder to inspect per-well failure modes and not overfit to easy wells.')\nlines.append(f'- **Generic deep learning:** Forum comments in {disc(701691, \\\"cv and lb correlations\\\")} suggest vanilla NNs struggle unless they encode spatial/sequential well-log structure. If using NN, formulate it around paths/series/candidates, not just row MLP features.')\nlines.append('- **Popularity bias:** The notebook-vote plot shows what people read, not what wins. Use it to find useful code, then judge by validation design and score evidence.')\nlines.append('')\nlines.append('## Practical target plan')\nlines.append('')\nlines.append('- **Day 1вҖ“2:** reproduce starter and local grouped CV; add per-well metrics and visualization for predicted vs true TVT on hidden-tail simulations.')\nlines.append('- **Day 3вҖ“5:** implement typewell GR alignment candidates: monotone linear path, DTW path, NCC shift/path, physics/tortuosity prior, and endpoint constraints.')\nlines.append('- **Day 6вҖ“8:** train Ridge/LGB/CatBoost residual models on OOF candidate-path features; compare by well-level CV and hard-well subsets.')\nlines.append('- **Day 9вҖ“10:** blend diverse OOF models; freeze a validation protocol; submit only a few public-LB probes to calibrate CV/LB without chasing it.')\nlines.append('- **Final stretch:** focus on robust per-well failure handling, deterministic notebook runtime, and private-test generalization rather than marginal public L